    "description": "Kankrar Jhaal by Krishna Mondal I রুরাল রেসিপির ত্রয়োদশ পর্ব । সুন্দরবনের পাখিরালয়ের বাসিন্দা শ্রীমতি কৃষ্ণা মন্ডল এর হাতের রান্না :  কাঁকড়ার ঝাল । \n\nThe crabs of Sunderbans are a gourmet delight cherished by food enthusiasts worldwide. Despite the daunting presence of tigers and crocodiles, fishermen brave the waters to procure these delectable river crabs.  Renowned for their superior taste compared to cultivated varieties, crabs from the rivers of Sunderbans are highly prized.  Among the myriad recipes, kankrar jhal (crab in a spicy gravy) stands out as a popular and easily prepared dish enjoyed across Bengal.\n\nRural local recipes are integral part of Intangible Cultural Heritage and needs to be preserved and promoted. We at banglanatak dot com have been working for the past 22+ years to safeguard and promote local cultural heritages in rural spaces across India. We are now launching a new initiative of documenting rural recipes and bringing them closer to the food lovers of the world. We request all to subscribe to our new channel Rural Recipes and stay tuned there to know, learn and try out local delicacies.  \n\nPresenter:  Debalina Bhowmick",
